The paper discusses the effect of changes in project-driven production systems and their impact on production flow variability. This topic is closely related to software engineering (cs.SE) and project management (cs.PM) as project-driven systems are common in these fields. Additionally, the paper mentions the application of lean practices, which is a concept often used in computer engineering (cs.CE) and robotics (cs.RO) to improve production efficiency. Finally, the paper uses mathematical models to measure and correlate the transient response of the production systems, which falls under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
